fields.long_definition: The 'areas' of your life that are important to you.
What you are doing, what you want to do, and what you did.
When you are doing. Time-based events and deadlines.

fields.long_definition: What you know - your information storage.
General container for anything of interest or importance.

fields.example: Tracuse App, Morning Checklist, Department Reorganization

fields.long_definition: What you use or general location for an action.
Who you commonly interact with.
Any group, such as a business, government agency, religious, or social organization.
A formal address/geolocation, or any informal point of interest.
fields.example: Office Address, School Address, The Garage

fields.long_definition: How to communicate with a Person or Entity, including phone, email, and social media.
fields.example: Carl's Work Contact, Carl's Home Contact, Main Office Contact

fields.long_definition: Any individual idea or thought about something you will do.
fields.example: Call the auto mechanic, Review Q1 sales, Be a better husband

fields.long_definition: Why you are doing what you are doing. Represents your values and vision.
fields.example: So we can take that vacation, So I will be healthy and happy

fields.long_definition: A record of what happened that you can use for next time.
fields.example: Okay rehearsal practice song more, Good meeting but next time have firm agenda

fields.long_definition: Track multiple events for an object to compare what you planned to do versus what you did.

fields.long_definition: A meeting, appointment, or any other time-based occurrence.
fields.example: Next Thursday All Day, May 13 2-3 PM

fields.long_definition: Simple alerts that can be used for short-term alarm or long-term tickler.
fields.example: Every Friday at Noon, July 4 9:30 AM

fields.long_definition: A fact or idea to remember.

Any electronic message, including emails, texts, and messages through social networking services.

fields.long_definition: Content from a streaming service provider, such as a blog or social networking post.
fields.example: Blog Post about Drum Technique, Facebook Post about Nephews
